Rebirth is the upcoming seventh studio album by American rapper Lil Wayne.
This album will be his rock debut.
The album is set to be released on April 7, 2009.
Background
The album was originally thought to be the re-release of his triple-platinum album Tha Carter III.
However on January 23, Lil Wayne told MTV that the album will not be a re-release, but will be his rock album debut.
He also stated the album will be released on April 7, 2009.
It is considered to be more of a 'continuation' of Tha Carter III than a new album.
The first single has been announced as "Prom Queen" and the track is produced by Infamous and Andrew "Drew" Correa.
The song made its official debut on January 27, appearing on Lil Wayne's MySpace page.
"Prom Queen" is available for purchase on all online music stores.
Lil Wayne peformed the single live for the first time during a concert in San Diego, which was streamed live on AT&Tâ€™s FREEdom of Choice and Mobile Music Facebook pages that evening.
"Prom Queen" rose to #17 on the Billboard Hot 100 charts.
Production
The first single, "Prom Queen", was produced by the duo of DJ Infamous and Drew Correa, notable for producing the Grammy nominated track from Tha Carter III, "Mr. Carter".
Production is also expected to come from Cool & Dre and Develop.
